
Overview of noun soma

The noun soma has 3 senses (no senses from tagged texts)
                                         
1. soma, haoma, Sarcostemma acidum -- (leafless East Indian vine; its sour milky juice formerly used to make an intoxicating drink)
2. Soma -- (personification of a sacred intoxicating drink used in Vedic ritual)
3. human body, physical body, material body, soma, build, figure, physique, anatomy, shape, bod, chassis, frame, form, flesh -- (alternative names for the body of a human being; "Leonardo studied the human body"; "he has a strong physique"; "the spirit is willing but the flesh is weak")
